    "created_at": "2016-08-09T07:16:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-09T08:25:45Z",
    "body": "Same problem: On Windows 7 and 10 Chinese font are rendered as rectangles while rendered correctly on Mac.\nElectron 0.37.60, pepflashplayer.dll 21.0.0.157.\n\nhere is a snapshot:\n\n![2016-08-09_15-10-26](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/782871/17507769/2157e21a-5e44-11e6-923e-f99d4c7c0019.png)\n\n## Any clues?\n\nupdate:\nI investigated the source code of Electron and Chromium, and found there are some questionable code may be the cause of above problem:\n\nIn [peper_flash_font_file_host.cc](https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/chromium_src/chrome/renderer/pepper/pepper_flash_font_file_host.cc)\nthere is a conditional compilation in method `PepperFlashFontFileHost::OnGetFontTable` which will not emit code on OS_WIN. And `GetFontTable` will not get called.\n\nIn Chromium source code\n[peper_flash_font_file_host.cc](https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src.git/+/master/chrome/renderer/pepper/pepper_flash_font_file_host.cc#71), there is code dealing with OS_WIN.\n\nThis is only my wild guess, please check it out.\n"
